Threat Actor: APT40 (Bronze President)

Background: 
    APT40 is a Chinese threat actor that has been active since at least 2009. 
    It employs tailored malicious software and spear-phishing emails as tactics to target entities within the defense, government, maritime, aerospace, education, and healthcare sectors.

Notable Incidents:
- Targeting Maritime Organizations
- Operation Cloud Hopper
- Espionage in Southeast Asia
EX. Really Incidents
(1) APT40 was involved in the cyberattacks against Microsoft Exchange servers in 2021. 
(2) APT40 was also behind the theft of sensitive data from US Navy contractors in 2018.

Attribution:
    APT40 is believed to be associated with the Chinese Ministry of State Security (MSS) and its Hainan State Security Department (HSSD). 
    The US and its allies have publicly attributed the Microsoft Exchange attacks to the MSS.
    
